            "answer_text": "If you mean THE Colosseum, in Rome, then no.  Spartacus died 141 years before construction on the Colosseum began.  There is also no mention of Spartacus ever actually visiting Rome.  He fought in Capua, about 120 miles (200 km) southeast of Rome, near Naples. ",
