            "answer_text": "A2A but there's not much to add; \"The Colosseum in Rome\" didn't exist when Spartacus lived and died. AFAIK there's no evidence that he ever fought at a contemporary venue in Rome, but I'm not a Spartacus biographer so I could possibly be wrong. Spartacus fought in Capua, which was a large and important Roman city in its own right. ",
